President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the reconstitution of the governing boards of five agencies under the Ministry of Transportation. They are the Nigerian Shippers’ Council (NSC), Nigerian Institute of Transport Technology (NITT), Maritime Academy of Nigeria, Oron (MAN, ORON), National Inland Waterways Authority (NIWA) and Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA). This is contained in a statement yesterday by the Director, Press and Public Relations of the ministry, Eric Ojiekwe. The chairman of the board of NSC is Lawal Sama’ila Abdullahi, with Rufai Ahmed Akambi, Usen Ekong Udoh, Otunba Oluseyi Oduntan, Violet Oliatan Williams and Mohammed Allamin Kam-Salem as members. Emmanuel Lyambee Jime is the Executive Secretary. The chairman of the board of NITT is Ejike Njeze, with . Amuda Seriki, Muhiydeen Sani Awwal, Paul Eluhaiwe, Gbenga Elegbele, and Senator Tutare Abubakar as members.   APC to consult Buhari, governors on timetable for primaries     Kachikwu seeks ADC presidential ticket     Odinkalu, Charley Boy, Onwenu, Bianca for talks with IPOB,…   The Director-General/CEO of the institute is Dr. Bayaro S. Farah. The chairman of MAN, ORON is Rear Adm. Jacob Adekunle Ajani, while Abdullah Nurudeen and Larry Odeh are members. The Rector of the academy is Commodore D. E. Effedua. The chairman of NIWA is Binta Masi Garba and the member of the board is Chibuike Ikenga. The Managing Director/CEO is Chief (Dr) George N. Moghalu. For the NPA, the chairman is Chief Akinwunmi Ricketts and members of the board are Senator Ayogu Eze, Ghazali Moh’d, Abdullazeez Nyako, Abdulwahab Adeshina and Mustapha Aminu Dutse. The Executive Director of Finance is Ms. Adenrele Susana Adeshina and the  Managing Director/CEO is Mohammed Bello Koko. The ministry stated that the inauguration of the boards by the Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi, will be conveyed in due course.